{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-post-js","path":"/experiences/elab/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><code>Rhode Island School of Design, JUN 2024 - present</code></p>\n<hr>\n<p>I believe that designers of the future need to embrace technologies in their design process. The mission of the ID E-Lab is to make technology an accessible creative medium. Leverging my technical competency in electronics engineering and programming, I host several workshops on relevent topics to empower the design community in RISD.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1cf418e5c9de89231c78fe0bb334523b/d2602/workshop.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"workshop\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/1cf418e5c9de89231c78fe0bb334523b/4b190/workshop.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1cf418e5c9de89231c78fe0bb334523b/e07e9/workshop.jpg 200w,\n/static/1cf418e5c9de89231c78fe0bb334523b/066f9/workshop.jpg 400w,\n/static/1cf418e5c9de89231c78fe0bb334523b/4b190/workshop.jpg 800w,\n/static/1cf418e5c9de89231c78fe0bb334523b/e5166/workshop.jpg 1200w,\n/static/1cf418e5c9de89231c78fe0bb334523b/b17f8/workshop.jpg 1600w,\n/static/1cf418e5c9de89231c78fe0bb334523b/d2602/workshop.jpg 4032w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Technical knowledge can be difficult to learn. In order for people to learn and practice in their own pace, I compile and consolidate all relevent resources and materials into well-organized websites as reference for students to go back after the workshop.</p>\n<p>List of past workshops:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/RISD-ID-E-Lab/IDSB-IoT\">IoT with ESP32</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/RISD-ID-E-Lab/IDSB-Motors\">Driving motors with Arduino</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/RISD-ID-E-Lab/IDSB-UIDev\">UI development with Flutter</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"E-Lab Research Assistant","subtitle":"Department of Industrial Design, RISD","meta_description":"Providing skill-build workshops for ID students on electronics, microprocessor and programming. Managing electronics parts and equipments in the ID E-Lab."},"parent":{"relativeDirectory":"experiences"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"22d02cf5-aaa6-505c-aaa2-526039cf8edd"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1328524562","1946181227"],"slicesMap":{}}